&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post is 18.75 hours per week.&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a 0.5 WTE (18.75 hours per week) Team Manager for the Specialist Perinatal Community Mental Health Team. The post is initially a fixed term position for 12 months and will be based at Melbury Lodge, Winchester.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The perinatal service is going through an exciting time with the implementation and rolling out of the NHS Long Term Plan, which seeks to transform specialist perinatal mental health services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will work alongside the existing Team Manager to lead the ongoing development and service design, as we continue to improve delivery of care in line with the national and local ambition.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a Registered Mental Health Nurse with significant community clinical and leadership experience, along with a passion for perinatal mental health. The post holder must also have the ability to network, establish and maintain positive working relationships.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;For informal discussions, please contact Liz James - Head of Nursing &amp; AHP&#39;s on 02380 874487 or &lt;span&gt;liz.james2@southernhealth.nhs.uk &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
